main event: Two or three objects were observed in the sky near South Laguna, California, on January 16, 1957, appearing, brightening, dimming, and disappearing over a period of one to two minutes.
interesting points: The objects were seen very low on the horizon in the WSW direction., The sighting involved visual observation and was enhanced by binoculars., Witnesses speculated that the objects could have been naval aircraft practicing night landings in the area., The report indicates that the objects appeared and disappeared in sequence., No photographs were taken during this observation.
sighted object: two or three bright objects in the sky
witness description: Civilian observers including a manager and others noting the lights' characteristics.
